<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Sample response: I know that the first statement is false because more students ride their bike than walk home.</li>
      <li>For example, if one question is completed as 
        <q>How many more students bike than walk?</q>  and 6 students bike and 4 students walk, students should explain how they know 2 more students bike than walk.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


